The paper presents a system for object relighting, which involves computer graphics (cs.GR) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques. The proposed shading model involves decomposition of the shading field, which is a common technique in computer graphics (cs.CG). The system also involves machine learning techniques for object modeling and perceptually-inspired shading, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories.
